{{Top|leg|title=''Chryya''-class very fast courier}}
The '''''Chryya''-class very fast courier''' was a type of heavy [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighter]] built by [[Hoersch-Kessel Drive, Inc./Legends|Hoersch-Kessel Drive, Inc.]], and used by the [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knights]] during the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]]. Whereas in this period, HKD were best known for the large [[Capital ship/Legends|capital ships]] used by the [[Trade Federation/Legends|Trade Federation]], the Chryya belonged to a design lineage of fast scouts that stretched back to the [[Delaya-class courier|''Delaya''-class courier]] of four thousand years earlier, also embodied by the contemporary [[Tavya-class armored picket|''Tavya''-class armored picket]] and [[Seltaya-class fast courier|''Seltaya''-class fast courier]]. Like those other ships, the Chryya took its class-name from a planet ending in -''a'', in this case [[Chryya]], once visited by [[Darth Maul/Legends|Darth Maul]].

The Chryya could be flown by a single [[Pilot/Legends|pilot]], but the cockpit also contained a seat and console for a dedicated [[Gunner/Legends|gunner]] to operate the turret-mounted [[Laser/Legends|laser]] cannon, and was large enough for entry and exit through a hatch in the forward hull, rather than simply an opening canopy. Six months before the [[Declaration of a New Order|fall of the Galactic Republic]], [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]] was using a modified Chryya as his personal starfighter, although it was stolen from him by [[Asajj Ventress/Legends|Asajj Ventress]] on [[Vjun/Legends|Vjun]].

